.  *Terrestrial edge and inference chips* (primarily for Tesla’s Optimus robots and vehicles).\n        2.  *Space-environment optimized chips* (for SpaceX\'s orbital AI compute infrastructure).\n\n### 2. Core Definition & Scale\n*   **Definition:** Terafab is an AI chip manufacturing initiative designed to vertically integrate the design, fabrication, and deployment of advanced logic and memory chips.\n*   **Scale & Capacity:** It is expected to be the **"world’s largest chip manufacturing facility,"** operating as a single closed-loop plant with the long-term goal of producing **one terawatt (1 TW) of compute hardware each year**.\n*   **Vertical Integration Strategy:** The facility will handle end-to-end production, including the design of lithography masks, fabrication of logic and memory chips, and advanced packaging. This closed-loop system is intended to allow for rapid testing, iteration, and scaling.\n\n### 3. Strategic Rationale\n*   **Supply Chain Mitigation:** A primary goal is to alleviate potential future chip shortages at SpaceX as it scales "orbital AI," reducing reliance on pure external foundries. \n*   **Hybrid Sourcing:** Despite Terafab\'s massive scale, the company notes it will *"continue sourcing a significant portion of our compute hardware from third-party suppliers,"* viewing Terafab as a complementary layer to secure the foundational chip stack.\n*   **Ecosystem Synergies:** The project leverages shared engineering resources, intellectual property, and infrastructure across Tesla and SpaceX, combined with Intel’s expertise in designing, fabricating, and packaging ultra-high-performance chips.\n\n### 4. Risk Factors & Disclosures\n*   **Capital Expenditure Risks:** Terafab is listed alongside Starship and AI data centers as a massive capital-intensive program. Prioritizing these long-term physical infrastructure investments may harm near-term financial performance and profitability.\n*   **Conflicts of Interest / Related-Party Transactions